# Derived from stock firmware dump wyze_floodlightv2C.bin (Wyze product
# HL_CAM3P, appver 4.53.3.9759, T41 "isvp_marmot" 4.4.94 kernel).
#
# VERIFIED FROM STOCK (dump):
#   SoC          : T41 (marmot). Board strings enumerate T41A/L/LQ/N/NQ/ZL/ZN/ZX;
#                  stock loads soc-nna.ko (NPU) + avpu -> "Q" NPU variant. NQ chosen
#                  to match the Wyze T41 sibling (wyze_cam4_t41nq).
#   Sensor       : gc3003a, MIPI 2-lane, 2304x1296@30, i2c0 @0x37, MCLK 27MHz.
#                  Stock: insmod sensor_gc3003a_t41.ko shvflip=1
#   ISP/encoder  : tx-isp-t41 isp_memopt=1 direct_mode=1 ivdc_mem_line=540;
#                  avpu clk_name=sclka avpu_clk=552000000 (BR2_AVPU_CLK_550MHZ nearest).
#   WiFi         : ATBM603x SDIO (stock atbm603x_wifi_sdio.ko) on msc1 (non-removable);
#                  2.4GHz-only per atbm_txpwer_dcxo_cfg (b/gn gains only) -> ATBM6031.
#                  Power/reset via mmc1_pwrseq reset-gpio GPC8 = GPIO 72 (in DTS).
#   SD card      : msc0, cd-gpio GPB26 = GPIO 58 (active-low), power GPB29 = GPIO 61.
#   Flash        : 16MB NOR on SFC0.
#   Console      : ttyS1 (uart1-pb), matches Wyze T41 convention.
#
# GPIO map RECOVERED from stock iCamera .dynsym + Binary Ninja decompilation of
# g_gpioParaMap (14 entries) and the gpio_write/gpio_read call sites:
#   62  reset button   in   (gpio_key_check_loop -> gpio_read(0x3e), active-low)
#   81  IR LED 850nm   out  (sdkgpio_irled_on -> gpio_write(0x51,1))
#   63  spk/amp enable out  (sdkspeaker_pa_set_mode -> gpio_write(0x3f)) -> AUDIO_GPIO
#   50  IR-cut A       out  (sub_46f5a8 "IRcut on" -> gpio_write(0x32,1))
#   49  IR-cut B       out  (same, gpio_write(0x31,1) 100ms later)
#   38  status LED (b) out  (sub_46f7f0 arg2 -> gpio_write(0x26))
#   39  status LED (a) out  (sub_46f7f0 arg1 -> gpio_write(0x27), boot level 1)
# Remaining map pins resolved by RE (NOT floodlight/PIR):
#   59 in  = SD card-detect (sdk_device_check_mmc_insert gpio_read(0x3b), "sd EJECT")
#   57 in  = SD "sd_cd_ex_pin" aux (gpio_dir_get/set(0x39))
#   60, 79 = not driven as GPIO by the app (coincidental constants only)
#   3x pin -1 = unpopulated (irled_2/"expand" stub returns -1).
#
# FLOODLIGHT + 3-ZONE PIR + SIREN are NOT SoC GPIOs: they hang off an external MCU
# on /dev/ttyS2 (UART2, uart2-pc = GPC13/14+GPC19/20; enabled in the DTS). Stock
# productservices/floodlight2/ttyS2/ttyS2.c opens ttyS2 @ 115200 8N1 raw and
# exchanges binary frames; PIR motion arrives as serial events dispatched to
# callbacks, floodlight brightness/PIRSensitivity/siren are sent as serial commands.
# -> A thingino userspace daemon on /dev/ttyS2 is required to drive motion+flood+siren.
# RMEM/NMEM copied from wyze_cam4_t41nq (same SoC); stock used isp_memopt=1.
